cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on developing a new system for scene text detection using deep learning models, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as character labeling, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of multi-task learning and rich supervised information indicates it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the development of a powerful low-level detector suggests it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of deep learning models and the development of a new learning mechanism suggest it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
